<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 06 at 6:10PM MDT  by NWS Billings</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of southwestern Custer,
northern Powder River and central Rosebud Counties through 715 PM
MDT...
At 608 PM MDT, the public reported strong thunderstorms along a line
extending from 14 miles east of Colstrip to 7 miles east of Broadus.
Movement was northeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Pea size hail.
SOURCE...Public.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Broadus, Volborg, Olive and Brandenberg.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
